<section id="Setting_a_Retirement_Date_for_an_Instance" remap="TID_22231">
	<title>Setting a Retirement Date for an Instance</title>
	<para> 
		<productname>CloudForms Management Engine</productname> allows you to retire an instance on a specific date.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Set a Retirement Date for an Instance</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				From <menuchoice><guimenu>Clouds</guimenu><guisubmenu>Instances</guisubmenu></menuchoice>, click on the instance that you want to set a retirement date for.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/2007.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Lifecycle</guilabel>), then click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/2008.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Set Retirement Dates</guilabel>).
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Either type in a date in the <guilabel>Retirement Date</guilabel> field or select one from the calendar control.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>Save</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>